@rem
@rem Abstract:
@rem   This is the command script responsible for the initial volume set 
@rem   tests in the extended volume set test.
@rem   This script performs the following:
@rem     - calls doinit.cmd 
@rem     	- calls getdat.cmd to get the ft componet info  
@rem     	- calls scendat.cmd to get the name of the logfile
@rem     - calls doformat.cmd to format the previously created ft componet
@rem     - performs a chkdsk on the volume set. 
@rem     - performs a dir test
@rem     - copies the next doextvol.2 script to donext.
@rem     - runs the extend.mst script to extend the volume set by one region.
@rem
@rem Author:
@rem   Mitch Millar  (a-mitchm) 4-13-94
@rem
@rem Revision History:
@rem *************************************************************************
@rem start phase 1

call doinit

call doformat %label% %fileSystem% %driveLetter1% %logfile%

call dosetmap %driveLetter1%:\foox1.bin %_fill_percent% %logfile%  

call dodir %driveLetter1% %logfile%  

call doendmd %driveLetter1%:\foox1.bin %logfile%  

call dochkdsk %driveLetter1% %fileSystem% %logfile% 

@rem setup for phase 2
copy doextvol.2 donext

mtrun extend.pcd /h
exit
